text.tspan: To start off, The main game uses a large map of the
Netherlands, featuring multiple provinces that can be
selected by clicking on them. When a province is
selected, it will appear in a darker shade. At the
bottom of the screen, there are multiple buttons that
house the most important features:
Another important feature in the map menu is the
"Rebel Meter", as its also a crucial part of the gameplay:
Each of these has a different function. Their uses are
explained in the summary! In the game, you can
choose to form alliances, buy colonies, and engage in
other activities. However, those are optional to do as
the primary objective is to build your army to conquer
all other provinces! The best way to learn how the game
works is through practice! I suggest playing on easy
mode, as each difficulty has their own upgrades, and in
easy mode, the game is much more easy-going when
exploring the mechanics for the first time. Keep in mind
that features may change in the future, considering the
game will continue to receive updates!

Æ’: These are Gulden, they can be used to buy
Upgrades and Provinces in the Main Menu. For
each difficulty, there is a seperate Upgrade Route,
so make sure you're playing in the Mode you've
spend your Gulden in! (Bought Provinces on the
other hand, can be played in each Difficulty!)
"Information": can only be used to see the stats
of the selected Province, while "Diplomacy" can be
used to Fight / Befriend the selected Province,
which takes up one of your "Action Points"!
"Next turn": can be used to regain "Action Points",
but also increases "Rebel Strength" (Which on Full
Power will cause a Rebellion in your last Province!)
"Enter Town": can be used to either increase your
Army or buy new Islands which earn tax-per-turn!
Battles: decrease "Rebel Strength" upon Difficulty!
Total # of allies determines your allied tax income!
3x enemy army required to make one surrender!
Turn on auto firing with the switch during battles!
If you find any bugs/glitches, plz contact @Ojee07!
